FOR SALE – “Request for Offers” closing Thursday 12th August 2021 at 4pm AWST.

2485 Pemberton Way, Karratha Industrial Estate is a fully leased industrial investment offered as part of a regional portfolio comprising assets in Kalgoorlie, Geraldton and Karratha, underpinned by an established national business with strong cash flows earned from a diverse range of industries.

The property is located within the Karratha Industrial Estate which is located approximately 6km east of the Karratha town centre.  

The property comprises a 10,400sqm site improved with some 2,460sqm* of functional office/warehouse improvements with generous laydown area providing good vehicle circulation.  

2485 Pemberton Way, Karratha Industrial Estate is offered for sale “in-one-line” with 63 Anderson Street, Webberton and 63 Kayili Road, West Kalgoorlie.

KEY FEATURES:
•	Improvements: 2,460sqm*
•	Site Area: 10,400sqm*
•	6km* to Karratha Town Centre
•	Zoned “Industry”
•	Good vehicle circulation
•	Dangerous goods store
•	26.4KW Solar Panel System
•	General Industrial zoned land with future development upside.
•	The assets represent key regional logistics hubs within ATOM's national distribution network.

LEASE SUMMARY:
•	Fully leased to Aqua Terra Oil and Mineral Service & Supply Co. Pty Ltd (Australia)
•	7-year lease term 
•	5-year option 
•	Passing income of $250,000 pa
•	3.0% annual rent reviews
•	Fully Recoverable Outgoings

*Approx

The property is offered for sale as part of a regional leaseback portfolio of three properties via a “Request for Offers” campaign closing Thursday 12th August 2021 at 4pm AWST. For a copy of the information memorandum, please contact the exclusive selling agents.
